## 1. Minimal `thespub-req.ttl` (Requirements Register)

```ttl
@prefix rdf:     <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs:    <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix dct:     <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@prefix skos:    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> .
@prefix req:     <https://w3id.org/requirement-ontology/rdl/> .
@prefix thespub: <http://test.linked.data.gov.au/def/thespub#> .
@prefix thesreq: <http://test.linked.data.gov.au/def/thespub/req/> .

#################################################################
#  ThesPub Requirements Register (minimal starter)
#################################################################

thesreq:RequirementRegister
    a dct:Standard ;
    dct:title "ThesPub Requirements Register (draft)"@en ;
    dct:description """
A small, illustrative register of requirements for the ThesPub profile,
intended to demonstrate how profile requirements can be modelled as
first-class RDF resources and linked to SHACL constraints.
"""@en ;
    dct:publisher <https://kurrawong.ai/> .

#################################################################
#  Requirement THES-01 — One prefLabel per language
#################################################################

thesreq:THES-01
    a req:REQ_0011 ;  # Requirement
    skos:notation "THES-01" ;
    rdfs:label "At most one skos:prefLabel per language tag per concept"@en ;
    dct:description """
For any skos:Concept, there MUST NOT be more than one skos:prefLabel
with the same language tag. This allows multilingual preferred labels
(one per language) while preventing conflicting preferred labels within
a single language.
"""@en .

#################################################################
#  Requirement THES-02 — Definition recommended, not required
#################################################################

thesreq:THES-02
    a req:REQ_0011 ;  # Requirement
    skos:notation "THES-02" ;
    rdfs:label "skos:definition is recommended but not mandatory"@en ;
    dct:description """
For thesaurus-style vocabularies, a skos:definition SHOULD be provided
for each skos:Concept where it adds clarity, but the absence of a
definition MUST NOT be treated as a validation error. Meaning may be
conveyed primarily via semantic relationships and placement in the
concept network.
"""@en .

#################################################################
#  Requirement THES-03 — Consider at least one altLabel
#################################################################

thesreq:THES-03
    a req:REQ_0011 ;  # Requirement
    skos:notation "THES-03" ;
    rdfs:label "Consider at least one skos:altLabel per concept"@en ;
    dct:description """
For user-facing thesauri, each skos:Concept SHOULD have at least one
skos:altLabel where appropriate, to support entry vocabulary and
synonym search. This is a recommendation, not a strict constraint,
and may be relaxed for very technical or tightly-controlled vocabularies.
"""@en .
```

